{% extends "layouts/base.twig" %}

{% block title %}Privacy Policy — Rumbo{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<div class="rj-container rj-legal-page">
    <p class="rj-eyebrow">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="rj-h1">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="rj-lead">Effective {{ "now"|date("F j, Y") }}. These terms are a working draft and should be reviewed by counsel before launch.</p>

    <h2>1. What We Collect</h2>
    <p>We collect the following categories of information when you use Rumbo:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Account details</strong> — your name, email address, and hashed password when
            you register; your organization name and billing contact if you join or create an
            organization.</li>
        <li><strong>Content you submit</strong> — public website URLs you analyze with Sounds Like
            Us; evaluation prompts, model configurations, and AI-generated responses you create in
            Eval; any free-text input you provide through platform features.</li>
        <li><strong>Usage and cost metering</strong> — which features you use, how often, and the
            token or credit consumption associated with each AI request, so we can enforce plan
            limits and calculate billing.</li>
        <li><strong>Technical logs</strong> — IP addresses, browser user-agent strings, request
            timestamps, and error traces retained for security monitoring and debugging. These are
            stored for a limited period and are not used for advertising.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use It</h2>
    <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Provide, operate, and improve the Rumbo platform and its tools.</li>
        <li>Process payments and manage subscriptions through Stripe.</li>
        <li>Send transactional emails such as email verification, password reset, and billing
            receipts.</li>
        <li>Respond to support requests and investigate reported problems.</li>
        <li>Detect and prevent abuse, fraud, and unauthorized access.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not use your content to train AI models and we do not sell your data to third parties.</p>

    <h2>3. AI Providers</h2>
    <p>
        Rumbo integrates with third-party AI providers to generate results. When you use Sounds
        Like Us, the text content of the public URLs you submit is sent to these providers. When
        you use Eval, your prompts and any reference content you configure are sent to the
        providers you select for comparison.
    </p>
    <p>Current AI providers include <strong>OpenAI</strong>, <strong>Anthropic</strong>, and
        <strong>DeepSeek</strong>. Each provider processes your submitted content under their own
        terms of service and privacy policies.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>Do not submit confidential, sensitive, or personally identifiable information
        through Rumbo features that are processed by AI providers.</strong> Treat submitted content
        as if it may be visible to those providers' data-handling systems.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Cookies and Local Storage</h2>
    <p>
        Rumbo uses a single first-party session cookie to keep you signed in. No third-party
        advertising or tracking cookies are set.
    </p>
    <p>
        Some UI preferences (such as theme selection or column visibility) are stored in your
        browser's local storage so they persist across visits without being sent to our servers.
        You can clear these at any time by clearing your browser's site data for Rumbo.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Sharing</h2>
    <p>We share your information only with the following categories of recipients, and only as
        necessary to operate the service:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Stripe</strong> — payment processing and subscription management.</li>
        <li><strong>Email delivery provider</strong> — sending transactional emails on our
            behalf.</li>
        <li><strong>AI providers</strong> — OpenAI, Anthropic, and DeepSeek, as described in
            section 3 above.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        Your data is never sold, rented, or shared with advertising networks, data brokers, or
        any party not listed here.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Retention and Deletion</h2>
    <p>
        You can delete your account at any time from your <a href="/account">account settings</a>.
        When you delete your account, your name and email address are anonymized and your
        organization memberships are removed. Content you created (such as eval runs and analysis
        results) may be retained in anonymized form for product integrity.
    </p>
    <p>
        Some operational records are retained even after account deletion, including audit log
        entries (for security and fraud purposes) and billing history (as required by law and for
        Stripe reconciliation). These records do not identify you by name or email after
        anonymization.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Security</h2>
    <p>We apply reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your information:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>All data in transit is encrypted using TLS.</li>
        <li>Passwords are stored as salted cryptographic hashes — we cannot recover your plaintext
            password.</li>
        <li>Access to production systems and user data is restricted to authorized personnel on a
            need-to-know basis.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        No system is perfectly secure. If you believe your account has been compromised, please
        reset your password immediately and contact us through the <a href="/support">support
        page</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Contact</h2>
    <p>
        If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or wish to make a data request, please
        visit our <a href="/support">support page</a>. We will respond within a reasonable
        timeframe.
    </p>
</div>
{% endblock %}
